description: Winged Victoria's Secret models will once again take the runway for the first official show since 2018.
title: Victoria's Secret fashion show returns following a 6-year hiatus

description: Rosita Milesi was honored with the U.N. Refugee Agency's Nansen Award for 40 years of activism. The U.N. calls her a “formidable refugee champion.” And she has life lessons to share.
title: Wise words from Sister Rosita, age 79: A math lover wins U.N. prize for refugee relief

description: In Arizona voters will decide whether local law enforcement should have the power to arrest people who cross the state's southern border illegally.
title: Proposal to allow Ariz. police to enforce immigration law to appear on state's ballot

description: Walgreens says about a quarter of its stores are unprofitable. Big pharmacy chains are struggling with growing retail competition and lower prescription payouts.
title: Walgreens will close 1,200 stores, hoping for a turnaround

description: At a town hall in Oaks, Pennsylvania, on Monday Trump ended the Q-and-A portion to ask the audience to remain and listen to music with him.
title: Trump town hall ends with 'musical-fest' while he stands on stage

description: Local election board members in Georgia cannot refuse to certify election results in any scenario, even if they report concerns about fraud or errors, a state judge has ruled.
title: Local board members in Georgia can't refuse to certify election results, judge rules

description: A pilot program in Alabama will distribute $280,000 from opioid settlement funds to support ‘grandfamilies’ formed to raise kids affected by the opioid epidemic.
title: A new way to support grandparents raising kids affected by the addiction epidemic

description: Vice President Harris will discuss her new proposals to win over Black male voters today at a town hall event. And, aid groups fear Israel is starving people in northern Gaza.
title: Harris courts Black male voters. And, worries that Israel is starving north Gaza

description: United Nations aid officials and Israeli human rights groups say Israel’s latest offensive in north Gaza forces residents to choose between leaving or starving. Israel allowed in food after Vice President Harris showed concern.
title: U.N. officials and rights groups warn Israel may seek to starve north Gaza

description: A trio of economists just won a Nobel prize for their insights into how democratic and other inclusive institutions are critical for a nation’s prosperity.
title: A Nobel prize for an explanation of why nations fail

description: A new technique for harvesting geothermal energy being pioneered in Utah has passed a significant milestone: Southern California Edison has contracted for enough of the energy to power 400,000 homes.
title: Petroleum drilling technology is now making carbon-free power

description: Destroying the roads would be in line with Kim Jong Un's push to cut off ties with South Korea and abandon the decades-long objective to seek a peaceful unification.
title: North Korea blows up parts of inter-Korean roads as tensions with South Korea soar
